bid_attachment_name: DLLR-FY2019-008 Racing CPA Services Purse Dedication.pdf
organization_name: Maryland Department of Labor, Licensing and Regulations
short_description: CPA Services for the Maryland Racing Commission (§9-1A-28
description: The State (DLLR) is issuing this solicitation for the purpose of obtaining CPA review services in order to comply with Md. Code Ann., State Govt. Article,  (9-1A-28) Purse Dedication Account, which prescribes amounts of operating assistance that may be authorized to support a specified minimum number of live racing days per year at each facility identified in Section 9-1A-28. description: Department of Health is accepting bids from qualified providers that can successfully provide ongoing hardware maintenance and troubleshooting for 100 Dell Venue Pro 11 tablets or similar to the specifications below.DESCRIPTION OF SERVICE - The contractor shall provide the following servicesFull mobile device management from Microsoft using Microsoft Intune Center -Or Comparable Product:Proactive monitoring and installation of service packs and updatesProactive monitoring for viruses and malware detectionRemote monitoring of usageRemote wipe and restoreRemote control for virus and malware scansRemote credentials management -user access managementFind my device featureCloud-based management portalEnsuring for only secure applications or sitesMonthly subscription and installation of Microsoft Intune -Or Comparable Product- for each device.Ongoing hardware maintenance and troubleshooting for each tablet configured. MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS:  The contractor shall meet the following minimum requirements:Must possess and provide proof of certifications related to the hardware-operating system named in this bid, and at least three professional references that demonstrate experience with similar projects.Ongoing services for each device including-Patch updatesTroubleshooting for Dell Venue Pro 11 tablets or similar -i.e. damaged devicesOn call support for lost passwordsFull mobile device management as specified aboveAdditional configuration/on-boarding of replacement and or additional tablets-Remote wipe and restore-Remote control for virus and malware scans-Remote credentials management, user access management -Find my device feature-Cloud-based management portal-Ensuring for only secure applications/sites

description: Sealed Bid 19-13-55064 Elkton West-Mill Run Service Area will be received until 130 PM August 22 2018 at the Purchasing Office 200 Chesapeake Blvd Ste 1400 Elkton MD 21921. This contract is for a project to construct the collection, pumping station, and conveyance infrastructure as shown on the Contract Drawings and described in the Specifications. The work herein includes but it not limited to construction and installation of the following-Approximately 2,190 linear feet of 12 inch PVC gravity sewer and associated manholesApproximately 9,035 linear feet of 8 inch gravity sewer and associated manholesApproximately 11,565 linear feet of 8 inch HDPE force main and associated blow off manholes and combination air/vac valve manholesAnd the 0.4 MGD peak flow Mill Run Pump Station.A pre-bid will be on July 25, 2018 at 1030 AM in the Perryville Conference Room County Administrative Building 200 Chesapeake Blvd, Elkton MD 21921. Bid packages on the County web-page (http://www.ccgov.org/dept_purchasing/index.cfm) for all vendors to download.  Bid packages may be purchased at a non-refundable cost of 75.00 per package for hard copies, or 10 for electronic copies (PDF format) provided on a compact disc. Additional specifications may be obtained by emailing ckamit@ccgov.org or calling 410-996-5396. Electronically submitted bid proposals will not be accepted.  All vendors wishing to submit a proposal should obtain an original set of documents or a compact disc from the Cecil County Purchasing Office.  If you choose to download the package from the website, you shall notify the Purchasing Office via e-mail or phone.  Not meeting this requirement may result in your proposal being considered as non-responsive.  Changes or addendums to this proposal and/or other documents will be posted to the proposal documents on the County web-page and sent directly to vendors who have obtained an original set of proposal documents or a compact disc or have obtained an electronic copy from the Purchasing Office.  The County is not responsible for information obtained from sources outside the Cecil County Purchasing Office, including downloads from the County website.  Vendors obtaining electronic copies of the proposal documents from outside the Purchasing Office will be directly responsible for obtaining updates, changes or addendums either from the updated web-page or by contacting the Purchasing Office. All questions or discussions concerning this bid, bid documents, specifications, etc., shall only be coordinated through the Purchasing Office.  The County shall not be responsible for information obtained outside the County Purchasing Office, concerning this or any other County bid, RFP, solicitation or quote. The Purchasing Office will provide vendor lists on the Cecil County web-site for all solicitations published unless a vendor/contractor provides a written request barring the disclosure of their information prior to specific proposal award.  Section 746 of Title VII of the Consolidated Appropriations Act of 2017 (Division A - Agriculture, Rural Development, Food and Drug Administration, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, 2017) and subsequent statutes mandating domestic preference applies an American Iron and Steel requirement to this project. All listed iron and steel products used in this project must be produced in the United States. The term iron and steel products means the following products made primarily of iron or steel- lined or unlined pipes and fittings, manhole covers and other municipal castings, hydrants, tanks, flanges, pipe clamps and restraints, valves, structural steel, reinforced precast concrete, and construction materials. The deminimis and minor components waiver apply to this contract. The Contract will be awarded to the lowest responsible, responsive bidder. Cecil County, Maryland reserves the right to reject any or all bids and to waive technicalities.  All contract awards are based upon budgetary constraint

bid_attachment_description: Elkton West Sanitary Sewer-Mill Run drawings
description: Sealed Bid 19-13-55064 Elkton West-Mill Run Service Area will be received until 130 PM August 22 2018 at the Purchasing Office 200 Chesapeake Blvd Ste 1400 Elkton MD 21921. This contract is for a project to construct the collection, pumping station, and conveyance infrastructure as shown on the Contract Drawings and described in the Specifications. The work herein includes but it not limited to construction and installation of the following-Approximately 2,190 linear feet of 12 inch PVC gravity sewer and associated manholesApproximately 9,035 linear feet of 8 inch gravity sewer and associated manholesApproximately 11,565 linear feet of 8 inch HDPE force main and associated blow off manholes and combination air/vac valve manholesAnd the 0.4 MGD peak flow Mill Run Pump Station.A pre-bid will be on July 25, 2018 at 1030 AM in the Perryville Conference Room County Administrative Building 200 Chesapeake Blvd, Elkton MD 21921. Bid packages on the County web-page (http://www.ccgov.org/dept_purchasing/index.cfm) for all vendors to download.  Bid packages may be purchased at a non-refundable cost of 75.00 per package for hard copies, or 10 for electronic copies (PDF format) provided on a compact disc. Additional specifications may be obtained by emailing ckamit@ccgov.org or calling 410-996-5396. Electronically submitted bid proposals will not be accepted.  All vendors wishing to submit a proposal should obtain an original set of documents or a compact disc from the Cecil County Purchasing Office.  If you choose to download the package from the website, you shall notify the Purchasing Office via e-mail or phone.  Not meeting this requirement may result in your proposal being considered as non-responsive.  Changes or addendums to this proposal and/or other documents will be posted to the proposal documents on the County web-page and sent directly to vendors who have obtained an original set of proposal documents or a compact disc or have obtained an electronic copy from the Purchasing Office.  The County is not responsible for information obtained from sources outside the Cecil County Purchasing Office, including downloads from the County website.  Vendors obtaining electronic copies of the proposal documents from outside the Purchasing Office will be directly responsible for obtaining updates, changes or addendums either from the updated web-page or by contacting the Purchasing Office. All questions or discussions concerning this bid, bid documents, specifications, etc., shall only be coordinated through the Purchasing Office.  The County shall not be responsible for information obtained outside the County Purchasing Office, concerning this or any other County bid, RFP, solicitation or quote. The Purchasing Office will provide vendor lists on the Cecil County web-site for all solicitations published unless a vendor/contractor provides a written request barring the disclosure of their information prior to specific proposal award.  Section 746 of Title VII of the Consolidated Appropriations Act of 2017 (Division A - Agriculture, Rural Development, Food and Drug Administration, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, 2017) and subsequent statutes mandating domestic preference applies an American Iron and Steel requirement to this project. All listed iron and steel products used in this project must be produced in the United States. The term iron and steel products means the following products made primarily of iron or steel- lined or unlined pipes and fittings, manhole covers and other municipal castings, hydrants, tanks, flanges, pipe clamps and restraints, valves, structural steel, reinforced precast concrete, and construction materials. The deminimis and minor components waiver apply to this contract. The Contract will be awarded to the lowest responsible, responsive bidder. Cecil County, Maryland reserves the right to reject any or all bids and to waive technicalities.  All contract awards are based upon budgetary constraint

description: The State (DLLR) is issuing this solicitation for the purpose of obtaining CPA review services in order to comply with Md. Code Ann., State Govt. Article,  (9-1A-28) Purse Dedication Account, which prescribes amounts of operating assistance that may be authorized to support a specified minimum number of live racing days per year at each facility identified in Section 9-1A-28. No bids will be accepted online or by fax or email. All bids must be either mailed to the address listed on the Key Information Summary Sheet or delivered in person prior to the the bid closing. **Please note that this is for a 2 year contract which will start on August 1, 2018 and terminate on July 31, 2020.**

short_description: CPA Services for the Maryland Racing Commission (§9-1A-28
description: The State (DLLR) is issuing this solicitation for the purpose of obtaining CPA review services in order to comply with Md. Code Ann., State Govt. Article,  (9-1A-28) Purse Dedication Account, which prescribes amounts of operating assistance that may be authorized to support a specified minimum number of live racing days per year at each facility identified in Section 9-1A-28. No bids will be accepted online or by fax or email. All bids must be either mailed to the address listed on the Key Information Summary Sheet or delivered in person prior to the the bid closing. **Please note that this is for a 2 year contract which will start on August 1, 2018 and terminate on July 31, 2020.**
